node.text:
7 exercises 3 rounds

DB RDL 10 full reps 10 bottom range
REVERSE LUNGES x12 each leg
BENT OVER ROW x12
LATERAL RAISE 1 & 1/4 rep x12
SINGLE LEG HIP THRUST x12 each leg
SIT UPS x12
BURPEES x12

Enjoy queens ✨

Home + Gym programs available in my LSF APP. Link in my bio @laurensimpson 📱

node.text:
-
CHOC CARAMEL OXYWHEY😱🍫🎉
-
I am SO excited to finally announce my very own protein flavour in collaboration with @ehplabs. You all know that I’ve been using Oxywhey for years now and it has been my ULTIMATE compliance buddy throughout every stage of my fitness journey, since the very beginning 😍.
-
From hitting my sweet tooth during WBFF World Championships preparation when living the calorie deficit life, to fuelling my booty gains when in a surplus🍑... To have my own flavour is an absolute dream come true💫!
-
What I’ve learned over the years is that the key to success on your health and fitness journey is to be prepared and not to deprive. Having Oxywhey has allowed me to stay complaint to my goals while not missing out on living my best life (hellooo, protein oats every morning!). Oxywhey has:
-
💫25g protein per serve.
💫Super probiotics (gut health, hair & skin).
💫B Vitamins (vitality and energy).
💫Alkalising vitamins and minerals for optimal health.
💫100% pure, lean, non-GMO whey protein.
💫All flavours are 100% natural.
-
Head to the LINK IN MY BIO to sign up to the exclusive mailing list to be the first to know when you can get your hands on my EHP CHOC CARAMEL Oxywhey 😋🍫
-
Link in my bio @laurensimpson

node.text:
FAT LOSS TRUTHS! 💪🏼💦

If fat loss is your goal, don’t lose sight of the basics that hold the key to getting results.

✅Before getting caught up on the latest fad diets and trends like keto, paleo, fasting etc...NAIL THE BASICS! 
Be in a calorie deficit.
Stop sweating the small stuff!

🙅🏼‍♀️Stop searching for quick fixes and shortcuts. Do it the right way…even if it’s the long way. Be patient.

🍫Find a diet you enjoy, that’s sustainable & allows for flexibility.

🏋🏼‍♀️Follow a structured training program that allows you to progress. Even if fat loss if your goal - still prioritise lifting weights and getting stronger.

👑No one is forcing you to embark on this journey. You have to want to do it for YOU.
@laurensimpsonfitness

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'FAT LOSS SIMPLIFIED'.

Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'THE MOST IMPORTANT FACTORS Stop being fixated on the scales Be in a calorie deficit Be patient & consistent BASICS 3H1 Prioritise lifting weights ದ Stop looking for quick fixes You dont need to suffer get esults'.

Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 10, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says '@LAURENSIMPSON THERE IS NO ONE MAGIC DIET OR FOOD FOR FAT LOSS. The best diet is the one you can stick too and be consistent with. Start educating yourself on the basics of nutrition. Energy balance is king.'.

Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '@LAURENSIMPSON Ⅲ|I Ⅲ|| ⅢI Ⅲ Ⅲ PROGRESS AND FAT LOSS ISN'T LINEAR. Your weight can and will fluctuate and plateau. Don't be impatient and quit! The scale is only one piece of data.'.

Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TOP TIPS FOR COMPLIANCE Stop making the same mistakes. ONE Create meal plan/days eating that not only fits your macros but you actually enjoy. You don't have to cut food groups and completely deprive yourself. TWO Even if fat loss is the goal still prioritise lifting weights. Fat loss doesn't mean you focus only on cardio high rep circuit training. Get strong & lift ladies. THREE Recognise that perfection doesn't exist. Life happens Take in your stride and if you slip up, get straight back to every new opportunity. @LAURENSIMPSON'.

node.text:
LOWER BODY @ HOME 🏠💪🏼

Hit SAVE and TAG a friend who is currently training from home.

As someone who has been training from home for 10+ weeks now due to lockdown and gym closures…I can tell you that whether training at home or in the gym…the same principles apply. I am still doing the same movement patterns, I am still finding ways to progressive overload (even when adding more weight isn’t an option) and I’m still pushing myself close to failure.

How are all my LSF HOME TRAINING QUEENS going? 👑

WORKOUT:

Glute focused superset:
A1) Single leg KAS glute bridge 3x 12
A2) DB hip thrust 3x 12 as 1 & 1/4 rep

Hamstring focused superset:
B1) DB romanian deadlift 3x 12
B2) DB Lying leg curl 3x 12 paused

Quad focused superset:
C1) B-stance squat 3x 12
C2) Sissy squat 3x 10

Enjoy 🥰

p.s. living in the @rarecollective_official tops. Wardrobe essential. 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
This top is Charcoal and I wear size small.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lauren Simpson on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Few snaps from the last week 📸🏠 Moving out of our home & getting it ready for auction.

Sorry for the lack of fitness content lately…my mind has been really preoccupied with getting life sorted in Sydney and ready for our move next month! Priorities often have to shift a little and this is just an example of one of those times.

If anyone missed it, Mark and I are moving to the Gold Coast! ✈️

While my mind is a bit of a blur - enjoy some happy snaps from the last week! 🥰 normal content will resume soon but I hope you have liked seeing something a bit different on my stories lately!

Love you all 😘

node.text:
HOW TO BUILD YOUR HAMSTRINGS 💪🏼🎯

Please hit SAVE + RESHARE if this was helpful.

To build and your grow your hamstrings you need to ensure you are training them through their functions of knee flexion and hip extension.

Knee flexion exercises include exercises like lying leg curl and seated leg curl. The difference with these two is that the seated leg curl is harder in the lengthened position (at the top where legs are extended) and the lying leg curl is hardest toward the shortened position (when legs are curled).

Hip extension exercises include Romanian deadlifts, good mornings, stiff leg deadlifts. These will train your hamstrings in the lengthened position. The exercises are hardest in the bottom position. Less knee bend = more hamstrings.

node.text:
LANDMINE EXERCISES 🎯Target: Lower Body

Here are some of my favourite landmine exercises that you can incorporate to spice up your training!

A landmine set up can be beneficial if you are training from home and have a barbell and weight plates. It can be an alternative when you don’t have heavier dumbbells.

👉🏼HACK SQUAT (you could also try this with elevated heels to increase the demand on your quads)
👉🏼SINGLE LEG HIP THRUST
👉🏼SINGLE LEG DEADLIFT
👉🏼REVERSE LUNGE
👉🏼ROMANIAN DEADLIFT
👉🏼GOBLET SQUAT

Have you tried any of these? Do you use the landmine?

node.text:
Romanian Deadlift VS Stiff leg deadlift ✌🏼

A common question I get asked is the difference between a Romanian deadlift & Stiff leg deadlift. Although they look like very similar movements there are key differences with range of motion, bar path etc that effect the muscles worked.

💪🏼Romanian Deadlift:
*Preferable if you want a greater degree of activation for your glutes + hamstrings. Hips are pushed further back so you get the deep stretch of the glutes at the bottom of the lift.

*Maintain a slight bend with your knees as you hinge your hips back & lower weight to your shins. You should have a neutral spine.

*Use your glutes when bringing the weight back up. Contract them at the bottom as you bring your hips back up to the start.

*Bar should be kept close to your body throughout the entire lift.

👊🏼Stiff leg deadlift:
*Preferable if you want higher degree of activation for hamstrings.

*Maintain a straight leg throughout the exercise. Keep your knees locked then bend at the waist and lower the weight toward the ground - stop when you feel your back start to round or you reach the floor.

*Focus on keeping your spine neutral and hamstrings stiff for maximum activation.

❓Differences:
*Knees are almost completely straight with the stiff leg whereas with RDL your knees are more bent to allow greater hip flexion.
*Weight is taken to the ground with stiff leg deadlifts whereas RDL stops around shins.
*Weight is kept closer to the body with RDL compared to Stiff leg where you allow the weight to drop straight down.
*I prefer lighter weight and higher reps for stiff leg due to the angle of the lift and then go heavier with lower reps for RDL.

Hope that helps 🤓👊🏼💗let me know! 
@laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
UPPER BODY @ HOME 🏠 using a long resistance band 💪🏼

Hit SAVE & tag a friend who might find this helpful. 👯‍♀️

Training at home definitely forces you to become creative with what you have available. You don’t need fancy gym equipment to get in a solid workout that’s for sure. I have been loving my @laurensimpsonfitness program and I’m already thinking of new exercises and methods to add into upcoming programs.

I love incorporating long resistance bands. In many cases they can be a great alternative to a cable machine you would use in the gym.

Heres a total upper body workout using the long resistance band.

💥When using bands I like to do a big pause at the peak contraction just to spend a little more time where your muscles are working hardest!

A1) Lat pulldown 3x 12
A2) Illiac pull down @coach_kassem  3x 12

B1) Rear delt row 3x 12
B2) Single arm bicep curl 3x 12

C1) Seated row 3x 12
C2) Rear delt low row 3x 12

D) Tricep extension 3x 15

Shop my programs, long bands and booty bands via link in my bio @laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
LOWER BODY @ HOME 🌶💓

SAVE this workout + give it a go. 👏🏼This is a minimal equipment workout and perfect for anyone training at home right now.🏠

This workout has the A & B series as trisets. This means three back to back exercises and then you rest. The last section is a superset C1 & C2, which is two exercises back to back.

I used to be really well known as a trainer who not only nailed the basics in programs but also had a really creative flair with fancier exercise variations. I want to bring a little of that back to my instagram. Spice things up on here a little. 🌶🌶

A1) Curtsy RDL 4x 10
A2) Straddle lift 4x 15
A3) Forward into reverse step lunge 4x 10

B1) Long band kickback 4x 12
B2) Long band standing abduction 4x 12
B3) Long band single leg curl 4x 12

*I attached my ankle cuff to the long band but you can also easily do these exercises without it.

C1) Lateral lunge 3x 12
C2) Squat jumps 3x 10/12/15 *sorry I didn’t film this one!

ENJOY!

Hope everyone is having a beautiful weekend 🌈

node.text:
WE ARE MOVING ✈️

It’s time for the next chapter in our life together. We are moving states (hello QLD) and have bought our dream home. Beyond excited as it’s been a long time coming to make this move. 🥳🏠

This also means that we are now in the process of selling our current home and it’s been a little chaotic behind the scenes getting the place ready for auction and also packing up our life! 📦

I’ll share more of our move from now on on my stories so watch this space! ❤️

@coachmarkcarroll

node.text:
Do you know what I think is cool….

Seeing women OWN who they are. Proudly embrace their body at all stages. Wear the damn shorts, rock that bikini, wear their favourite sports bra….even if not at their leanest.

Seeing ladies upping their calories to maintenance and above. Breaking free of constantly living in a calorie deficit and the extreme dieting mindset.

Seeing all my bad aass girls lifting weights & having strength goals. There is something so empowering about saying goodbye to endless hours of cardio & focusing on lifting weights and getting stronger. Exercise should not be purely to burn calories or to look ‘thin’.

Seeing women building empires & chasing career goals.

Seeing women supporting each other instead of tearing each other down. Her win does not mean your loss. Cheer loud for that girl next to you...even if she is pretty, even if she is smart, even if she is successful, even if you aren’t happy with where you are at right now...because one day you will really need that applause too.

I love this quote:

‘A glowing woman can help other women glow and still be lit.’ 👑✨

FIX YOUR FORM: GOBLET SQUAT ❌✅

SAVE + RESHARE! 🙏🏼

Goblet squats have been a staple in my programs lately, especially when working out from home. To make them extra savage you can add a long restiance band around you) 
It’s also a great exercise for beginners to train the squat movement pattern.

Weight is in front making it easier to keep your torso upright and for balance.

💡I am doing it with a heel elevation to help with ankle mobility which allows you to sit deeper and also makes it easier for your knees to travel forward.

❌Common mistakes:
Weight is held too far forward away from chest
Leaning torso forward
Weight held too low
Core not engaged

✅Good form cues:
Weight is held close to chest
Maintain a neutral spine
Torso upright
Knees track out in line with toes
Core braced

I hope this was helpful. Let me know what other HOME exercises you would like a breakdown on! 🙏🏼

@laurensimpsonfitness
